ZH: 我要在法庭上作出陈述。
EN: I need to make a statement in court.

ZH: 这份报告是关于我们的调查结果的陈述。
EN: This report is a statement of our investigation findings.

ZH: 他发表了一份公开陈述，解释了他的立场。
EN: He made a public statement explaining his position.

ZH: 论文的摘要以一句简短的陈述开始。
EN: The abstract of the paper begins with a concise statement.

ZH: 请在陈述中清楚地表达你的意见。
EN: Please express your opinion clearly in the statement.

ZH: 他的陈述引发了一场激烈的辩论。
EN: His statement sparked a heated debate.

ZH: 我希望在陈述中提供更多证据支持我的观点。
EN: I hope to present more evidence supporting my viewpoint in the statement.

ZH: 陈述书需要在一周内提交给法院。
EN: The statement of claim needs to be filed with the court within a week.

ZH: 他的陈述被认为是非常有力的。
EN: His statement is considered to be very forceful.

ZH: 她的陈述表达了对受害者家庭的感激之情。
EN: Her statement expressed gratitude towards the victim's family.

ZH: 在陈述中，他详细描述了事故的经过。
EN: In the statement, he provided a detailed account of the accident.

ZH: 你的陈述中应该包含完整的事实和细节。
EN: Your statement should include all relevant facts and details.

ZH: 这是一份关于项目进展的陈述。
EN: This is a statement about the progress of the project.

ZH: 每个证人都被要求提供书面陈述。
EN: Every witness is required to provide a written statement.

ZH: 我们会对你的陈述进行调查。
EN: We will investigate your statement.

ZH: 请在你的陈述中描述你的经历和见解。
EN: Please describe your experiences and insights in your statement.

ZH: 陈述中的事实应该是可核实的。
EN: The facts stated in the statement should be verifiable.

ZH: 你的陈述应该精简明了，以便容易理解。
EN: Your statement should be concise and easy to comprehend.

ZH: 律师建议我写一份陈述来详细说明我的案情。
EN: The lawyer advised me to write a statement explaining my case in detail.

ZH: 我已经准备好在法庭上做出陈述。
EN: I am ready to make a statement in the courtroom.
